    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 643 (st2941): __neg__, __pos__, __abs__ dict-presence checks for struct types."
    - "struct.Struct is a C extension type for packing/unpacking binary data; struct.error is an exception subclass — neither defines unary negation, positive, or absolute value operators."
    - "Verified types: struct.Struct, struct.error."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

